==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Easel
<hw>Ea"sel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>ezel</ets>
ass, donkey, hence, easel, or G. <ets>esel</ets>; akin to E.
<ets>ass</ets>. See <er>Ass</er>.]</ety> <def>A frame (commonly) of wood
serving to hold a canvas upright, or nearly upright, for the painter's
convenience or for exhibition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Easel picture</b></col>, <col><b>Easel
piece</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a painting of moderate size such as is made
while resting on an easel, as distinguished from a painting on a wall or
ceiling.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Easeless</ent>⟦br⟧
